    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "When Ahijah heard the sound of her feet entering the door (the participle בּאה, according to the number and gender, refers to the אשּׁה implied in רגליה, vid., Ewald, 317, c.), he addressed her by her name, charged her with her disguise of herself, and told her that he was entrusted with a hard saying to her. קשׁה (cf., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 12:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is equivalent to קשׁה חזוּת; for the construction, compare Ewald, 284, c.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
